---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Header from "../components/layout/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/layout/Footer.astro";
---

<Base
    title="About"
    description="Learn about the Atmosphere community and AT Protocol."
>
    <Header slot="header" />

    <article class="about-page section">
        <div class="container container--narrow">
            <h1>About the Atmosphere</h1>

            <div class="prose">
                <p>
                    The <strong>Atmosphere</strong> is the growing community of people
                    and projects building on
                    <a href="https://atproto.com">AT Protocol</a> — the open, decentralized
                    protocol behind <a href="https://bsky.app">Bluesky</a>
                    and a growing ecosystem of apps, tools, and services.
                </p>

                <p>
                    atmosphere.community is the community front door. We
                    aggregate blog posts from the community, surface upcoming
                    events organized by our regional communities, and connect
                    you with those local atproto groups around the world.
                </p>

                <h2>Community Fund</h2>
                <p>
                    The <a
                        href="https://opencollective.com/atprotocoldev/"
                        rel="noopener noreferrer"
                        target="_blank">AT Community Fund</a
                    >
                    supports projects, events, and infrastructure that strengthen
                    the ecosystem. It has funded community conferences, developer
                    tools, and educational resources.
                </p>

                <h2>Get involved</h2>
                <p>
                    There are many ways to participate in the Atmosphere
                    community:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <a href="https://blog.atmosphere.community"
                            >Subscribe to the blog</a
                        >
                        — including email newsletter
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a href="https://discourse.atprotocol.community"
                            >Join the community forum</a
                        >
                        — discussions, working groups, and community coordination
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Contribute to community open-source projects and
                        community infrastructure <a
                            href="https://tangled.org/did:plc:lehcqqkwzcwvjvw66uthu5oq"
                            >Tangled @atmosphere.community</a
                        > and <a href="https://github.com/ATProtocol-Community"
                            >GitHub @ATProtocol-Community</a
                        >
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/atmosphere.community"
                            >Follow our account <code
                                >@atmosphere.community</code
                            ></a
                        >
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a href="/communities">Find a local community</a> near you
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <h2>Contributing to this site</h2>
                <p>
                    The atmosphere.community site uses atproto-native features
                    to highlight community projects of all kinds. You can
                    contribute with ideas, code, design by joining us in the <a
                        href="https://discord.com/channels/1097580399187738645/1494842659846488256"
                        >#atmosphere-community-website</a
                    > channel in the Discord chat. The Github codebase is at <a
                        href="https://github.com/ATProtocol-Community/atproto-community"
                        >@ATProtocol-Community/atproto-community</a
                    >, including issues.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </article>

    <Footer slot="footer" />
</Base>

<style>
    .about-page h1 {
        margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    }

    .prose {
        font-size: var(--text-base);
        line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
        max-width: 65ch;
    }

    .prose h2 {
        margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
        margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    }

    .prose p + p {
        margin-top: var(--space-base);
    }

    .prose ul {
        margin-top: var(--space-base);
        padding-left: var(--space-lg);
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: var(--space-sm);
    }

    .prose li {
        line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    }

    .prose code {
        font-size: 0.9em;
        background: var(--neutral-100);
        padding: 2px 6px;
        border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    }

    .prose strong {
        font-weight: 600;
    }
</style>
